(1663, '아무 N도', 'nothing/no--Nnegating person, thing or place; used w/ neg. verbs; used with compound particles)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch6'),
(1664, 'V이/히/리/기 -(피동=passive)', 'irregular passive Vsactive voice V > passive voice V (어 있다 used with some to indicate continuous states)Here is a simple chart explaining how to form the passive voice in Korean based on verb stem endings and the corresponding passive suffixes: V Endingsuffixexamplepassive ex.meaning vowel, ㅎ, ㄲ-이-보다 (to see)보이다to be seen ㅂ, ㄱ, ㄷ, ㅈ, ㅍ-히-잡다 (to catch)잡히다to be caughtㄹ-리-열다 (to open)열리다to be openedㄴ, ㅅ, ㅁ, ㅊ-기-담다 (to put in)담기다to be put inother consonants-이-닫다 (to close)닫히다to be closed Additional Notes: For 하다 verbs, passive is formed by replacing 하다 with 되다 or 받다 (e.g., 준비하다 → 준비되다, 사랑하다 → 사랑받다). Some verbs undergo stem vowel changes when forming passive (e.g., 바꾸다 → 바뀌다). Passive verbs emphasize that the subject receives the action. This suffixation method is the most common way to form passive verbs in Korean. Example Sentences: 쥐가 고양이에게 잡혔어요. (The mouse was caught by the cat.) 문이 열렸어요. (The door was opened.) 편지가 배달되었어요. (The letter was delivered.)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch6'),
(1665, 'V았/었다가', 'Ved, then turned around and Vafter subj completes 1 action, do another action (actions must be opposites or related actions)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch7'),
(1666, 'A(으)ㄴ데도; V는데도; N인데도', 'although / despite A, V, N ... [cl2 oddly enough]Situation arises in 2nd cl. that could not be predicted based on 1st cl. (past tense use -았/었 & 였/이었)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch7'),
(1667, 'A/V더니', 'and/but now; and thenobservation of s1 else''s past action & change undergone w/time (broadly entails ''changes with passage of time'')', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch7'),
(1668, 'V도록 하다', 'you better do V/make sure you do Vemphatical commands or 1''s intention in a formal setting (sentence has same basic meaning without)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch7'),
(1669, 'A다고요; Vㄴ/는다고요; N(이)라고요', 'What?! ...A, V, N, you say?reconfirming what was said or astonishment (can be used with past, future)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch8'),
(1670, 'V(으)라고요', 'What?! ...you want me to V you say?reconfirming an imperative or astonishment', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch8'),
(1671, 'V자고요', 'What?! You say let''s V?reconfirming a propositive or astonishment', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch8'),
(1672, '아무리 A/V아/어도', 'no matter how much A/Vstrongly emphasizing action/state occurs regardless of another action/state', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch8'),
(1673, 'A/V아/어야 할 텐데(요)', 'hoping that / afraid that A/Vhoping st will happen & worrying about it', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch8'),
(1674, 'N을/를 위해(서); V기 위해(서)', 'for the sake of N/Vaim/purpose of action (usually written/formal situations; (으)려고 = informal version)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch9'),
(1675, 'V아/어지다', 'to become/get Vsubj changed by external forces (used with limited set of Vs)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch9'),
(1676, 'A(으)ㄴ데도, V는데도, N인데도,불구하고', 'Even despite/though A, V, N...''regardless/despite'' emphasizing assumption/expectation about st followed by different result (same as 었/았는데도; usually written/formal)', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch9'),
(1677, '(1) N에 대해(서), (2) N1에 대한 N2', '(1) about N (2) N2 about N1N will be topic of thought/conversation/presentation', 'grammar', '3A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch9'),
(1678, 'A/V던', 'was Ving / used to Vthinking back on past event; past action remains unfinished and can be restarted or continued', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch10'),
(1679, 'A/V잖아요', 'as you (should) knowconfiming s1 knows st they are assumed to know OR reminding s1 of st they are assumed not to remember', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch10'),
(1680, 'V(으)ㄹ 생각이다 [계획/예정]', 'thinking of/planning to/scheduled to Vfuture plans/thoughts (예정 only for specific set future event)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch10'),
(1681, 'V(으)려면 멀었다', 'far away from Vingaction that will occur a a time perceived as distant', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch10'),
(1682, 'V이/히/리/기/우 -(상동)', 'make/cause/do st for another (irreg. causative)Subj directly causes action to direct or indirect object (some w/ =게 하다 instead)Here is a simple chart explaining how to form causative verbs in Korean by adding the suffixes -이, -히, -리, -기, -우 to verb stems. These suffixes turn an active verb or adjective into a causative form, meaning "to make/let/cause someone or something to do" the action. endingsuffixex. activecausativemeaningVowel, ㄱ, ㅎ-이보다 (to see)보이다to show, make seeㄱ, ㄷ, ㅂ-히닫다 (to close)닫히다to make closeㄹ, ㄷ-리열다 (to open)열리다to make openㄴ, ㅁ, ㅅ-기신다 (to wear)신기다to make wearvarious exceptions-우자다 (to sleep)재우다to put to sleepHow to Use The causative verb means the subject causes or lets someone/something else do the action. Structure: Noun + 을/를 + V-(이/히/리/기/우) + 어/아요 Example: 친구를 웃기다 (to make a friend laugh) 아이를 재우다 (to put a child to sleep) Active SentenceCausative SentenceEnglish Translation 영희가 웃어요.철수가 영희를 웃겨요.Younghee laughs. / Cheolsu makes Younghee laugh.아이가 자요.엄마가 아이를 재워요.The child sleeps. / Mom puts the child to sleep.새가 날아요.바람이 새를 날려요.The bird flies. / The wind makes the bird fly.', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch11'),
(1683, '(1) N1이/가 N2를 V-(상동) (2) N1이/가 N2에게 N3을/를 V-(상동) (3) N1이/가 N2의 N3을/를 V-(상동) (4) V-(상동)+ 주다', '*Causative Patterns* PatternKoreanEnglishExplanation (1) N1이/가 N2를 V-(상동)엄마가 아기를 재웠다.Mom put the baby to sleep.Subject (Mom) causes object (baby) to do action (sleep). Causative verb 재우다 used.(2) N1이/가 N2에게 N3을/를 V-(상동)선생님이 학생에게 책을 읽혔다.The teacher made the student read a book.Subject (teacher) causes indirect object (student) to perform action on N3 (book).(3) N1이/가 N2의 N3을/를 V-(상동)아버지가 아이의 머리를 깎았다.Father cut the child''s hair.Subject (father) causes an action on N2’s (child’s) N3 (hair). Possessive structure used.(4) V-(상동) + 주다친구가 나를 웃게 해 주었다.A friend made me laugh (for me).Causative verb 웃기다 used with -게 하다 + 주다 to express causing action for benefit.Notes on each pattern: N1이/가 N2를 V-(상동) The simplest causative structure: subject causes the object to do the action. Uses causative verb directly with the object marked by 을/를. N1이/가 N2에게 N3을/를 V-(상동) Subject causes an indirect object (N2) to perform an action on N3. N2 marked with 에게 (to), N3 marked with 을/를 (object). N1이/가 N2의 N3을/를 V-(상동) Subject causes an action on a possessed noun (N3) of N2. Shows possession with 의. V-(상동) + 주다 Adds nuance of doing the causative action for the benefit of someone. Often uses the causative verb stem + -게 하다 + 주다.', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch11'),
(1684, 'A다면; Vㄴ/는다면;N(이)라면', '(1) if A/V/N happens then ... (2) Whereas/while (contrasting/opposite things)(1) hypothesizing about very unlikely/unrealistic potential situation/condition & what action/state would occur if it were true (만약(에) or 만일(에) = emphasis)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch11'),
(1685, '무엇이든(지); 무슨 N(이)든지', 'any-- [is ok]selecting b/t variety of options, choice doesn''t matter (also: 언제/어디(에)/누구/얼마+든지)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch11'),
(1686, 'V았/었더니', 'as a result of V.../[connecting indir. quotes]result/situation occurs after past action; usually cl1 is cause; cls different subjects (if cl1 is 1st person, cls can have same subj)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNu.lvl.3B.ch12'),
(1687, '얼마나,A(으)ᄂ지 / V는지,모르다', 'don''t even know how much [very] A, Vemphasize action/state', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNu.lvl.3B.ch12'),
(1688, 'A(으)ㄴ; V는; N인;모양이다', 'A/V/N is the shape of it [seems]conjecture about situation based on observation (only indirect evidence; form/written; V(으)ᄂ/는/(으)ᄅ = past/pres/fut)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNu.lvl.3B.ch12'),
(1689, 'A/V아/어야; N이어야/여야', 'have to A/V/N so cl2 can ...condition required for state/action to occur (N(이)라야 also; not followed by imperative/propositive; combo w/ -만 for emphasis)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNu.lvl.3B.ch12'),
(1690, 'A/V(으)ㄹ까 봐', 'worried/afraid that A/Vworry about potential unwanted future event; reason for action/concern (do not use future tense in 2nd cl.)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch13'),
(1691, 'V고 있다', 'is wearing/Ving; be doing V; be in the middle of doing Vcontinuation of verb states / progressive aspect; also ''wearing'' (also: wearing V고 + action verb)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch13'),
(1692, 'A/V았/었어야 했는데', 'should have done/beenconjecturing regret about past events & what may/may not have been if events hadn''t occurred', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch13'),
(1693, 'V도록', 'so that/in order to/be sure to/to force to/to the extent of Purpose / So that... / In order to... Indicates the purpose or goal of an action. Extent / Degree / To the point that... Expresses the degree or extent something happens. Time / Until... Indicates a time limit or duration until something happens. purpose/reason for following action (-게 also used w/ same meaning; w/ time expressions = -까지 typeStructureExampleEnglish PurposeV + 도록 하다늦지 않도록 공부하세요.Study so that you are not late.Extent / DegreeV + 도록울도록 감동했어요.Was moved to the point of tears.Time / UntilV + 도록 하다해가 질 때까지 놀도록 하세요.Play until the sun sets.', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch13'),
(1694, '하도 A/V아/어서', 'so much A/V thatemphasizing extent; often w/ adverbs 만히, 오래, 열심히', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch14'),
(1695, 'A/V았/었던', 'past tense adnomial (completed action doesn''t persist)thinking back on completed past situations/events experienced 1-2 times', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch14'),
(1696, 'A아/어하다', '3rd person feels A3rd person state of mind/feelings (*In 1st person, expresses feelings objectively)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch14'),
(1697, 'A/V(으)면 A/V(을) 수록', 'the more... the more...action/state repeated, or degree becomes more severe (''the more... the more...)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch14'),
(1698, 'V게 하다', 'let/force to VSubj indirectly cases action to object', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch15'),
(1699, 'A/V(으)ㄹ걸(요)', 'I guess/bet thatlight rebuttal/surprise when conjecturing', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch15'),
(1700, 'V는 길에', 'on the waydoing 1 action allows opportunity for another action which isn''t original intention', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch15'),
(1701, 'A/V지 않으면 안 되다', 'must do/be V/ASt must be done or situation is required (form/writ)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch15'),
(1702, 'N만 하다', 'the size/quality of N''size/quality'' by comparing 2 things that are similar (also as exaggeration when things are not the same)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch16'),
(1703, 'V(으)ㄹ 생각도 못 하다', 'can''t even think about Vingaction impossible b/c of reasons in 1st cl (use with -어서 & -기때문에; w/ -(으)면 = -아.어야 -을 수 있다)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch16'),
(1704, 'V(으)ㄹ 만하다', 'V is worth doing/might as well do Vst ''worth'' doing (also, st not good, but acceptable)', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch16'),
