(1709, 'N(이)라고 (해서) 다 A(으)ㄴ/V는 아니다', 'not all N are/do A/Vexception to common thought (abbr. -다고/(이)라고; 헤서 dropped in spoken lang.)\학생이라고 해서 다 시험을 잘 보는 것은 아니다.Not all students do well on exams.부자라고 해서 다 행복한 것은 아니다.Not all rich people are happy.', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch17'),
(1710, 'A다니까(요); Vㄴ/는다니까(요); N(이)라니까(요)', 'I''m telling you A, V, N...reconfirming with emphasis what was just said', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch18'),
(1711, 'V고 말다', 'ended up Vingoccurrence w/o intention OR achievement took effortThe structure emphasizes that despite intentions, the action happened in an undesired or unexpected way.시험 공부를 안 했더니 결국 떨어지고 말았어요.I didn’t study for the exam, and I ended up failing it.', 'grammar', '3B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3B SNU.lvl.3B.ch18'),
