(1777, 'A다면서요? V/(ㄴ)는다면서요? N(이)라면서요?', '''is it true that?'' (asking to confirm info from 3rd party source)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(1778, 'V다 보면', '''if you keep doing V, then...'' (situation can/will follow the continuation/repetition of action. Use with expressions of possibility 2nd cl. No not follow w/ past tense)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(1779, 'N(은)는;A다는;V(ㄴ)는다는;것이다/점이다', '''The thing about N is that A/V'' (explaining in detail meaning/content of topic. subj of embedded cl. takes 이/가)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(1780, 'V는 대로; N대로', '''just like/based on/as soon as'' (st done ''exactly as'' or ''a situation/appearance is like'' another)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(1781, 'N -적', '''N-like'' (-적 can be added to some N of Chinese origin, turns N>adj. related to/having properties of N)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(1782, '어찌나/얼마나 A(으)ㄴ지;V는지', '''so/such A/V than...'' (degree so severe leads to following result)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(1783, 'A/V(으)ㄹ 정도로/정이다', '''to the extent that A/V'' ''to the point where A/V'' (metaphorically emphasizing degree)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(1784, 'A/V다가는', '''if A/V continues, then [neg. result]'' (neg/undesirable situation could occur if action continues/repeats. use with expressions of possibility 2nd cl. hypotheticals about present/future use: 았/었다가는)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(1785, 'A/V(으)ㄹ 뿐만N뿐반 아니라', '''not only... but also...'' (additional info. . info. 1st & 2nd cl, must both be pos. or both neg.)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(1786, '과-N', '''excessive'' (N prefix meaning overly, excessively)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(1787, 'V(으)나 마나', '''no use doing V'' ''even w/o doing V'' (doing or not doing V will not influence a result. often combo w/ 아/어 보다, cannot negate V)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(1788, 'V는 바람에', '''as a result of V [cl.]'' (action cause of neg./undesirable effect on situation. tense marker at end of sent.)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(1789, 'N(이)라는 N', '''It''s an N called N'' (introducing what st is called; appple라는 fruit = a fruit called apple)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(1790, 'N에 비해서', '''compared to'' / ''for [her age]'' (comparing/providing standard)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(1791, 'A/V기는커녕; N은/는커녕', '''let alone A/V/N ..[st harder/opposite than expected]'' (1. situation obviously impossible & another, comparatively easier, is also hard 2. doing opposite than expected in 2nd cl.; A/V는 것은 고사하고 & N은/는 고사하고 same meaning)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(1792, 'A/V(으)ᄅ 게 뻔하다; N일 게 뻔하다', '''evidently/surely/obviously'' (certainty about a neg. action/result based on evidence; 1st person can''t be will or intention, only st ''forced/unchosen'')', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(1793, 'A(으)ㄴ; V는 반면에', '''whereas [on the other hand]'' (2 situations are opposing facts; difference in character of 1 subj, or b/t 2 subj)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(1794, 'A/V(으)ㄹ 수밖에 없다', '''no choice but to V'' ''expected to be A'' (no other possibility/choice but to do V, be in state of A)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(1795, 'N-스럽다', '''N-like'' (affix turning N into Adj having the qualities of N)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(1796, 'A/V고; N이고; 해서', '''among other things, b/c A/V/N...'' (situation one of several reasons for action. Also: listing multiple reasons among others:N도 A/V고 해서A/V기도 하고 해서For ?s & suggestions = 고 한데 or 고 하니까)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(1797, 'A다더니; V(ㄴ)는다더니', '''I''ve heard that...''/They say that...'' (thinking back on ''heard info'' b4 thoughts. Used quoting idioms & proverbs b4 explaining thoughts. long form = 다고 하더니)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(1798, 'A/V기 마련이다', '''It''s natural that / bound to V'' (result of action/situation is normal/to be expected. Used for ordinary/common things. also: 게 마련이다)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(1799, 'V다 보니(까)', '''after Ving, I''ve come to think...'' (continuation/repetition led to a result. 아/어지다 &/or 게 되다 often follow)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(1800, 'A/V기는요; N (이)기는요', '''not really/no need to'' (answering ?s w/ neg. response, always present tense, also humbly responding to compliments)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(1801, 'A/V든지 A/V든지; N(이)든지 N(이)든지', '''either ... or ... [is OK]'' selecting among options is irrelevant; V든지 말든지 used w/ neg. connotations; short form = -든, can''t be used w/ future; past = V았/었든지 .." for emphasis = -든지 안 -든지; -든지 말든지; -든지 못 -든지', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(1802, 'N(이)야말로', '''indeed / the very / exactly'' (emphasize previous N, or st is undeniable fact)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(1803, '여간 A(으)ㄴ / V는 것이 아니다; 여간 A/V지 않다', '''not an ordinary ...'' (emphasizing situation is not just the usual; same as 아주/매우 A/V; 여간 always w/ negation; writ/form)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(1804, 'V(으)ㄹ 거리; N거리', '''something to V'' ''something used for N'' (suffix meaning something, w/ N sometimes has no meaning other than emphasis)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(1805, 'A/V/N(이)더라도', '''even if'' A/V/N(strong emphasis on hypothetical, doesn''t affect sit''n in 2nd cl.; long form = 다(고) 하더라도; past A/V았/었더라도 N였/이었더라도)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(1806, 'V(ㄴ)는;A다고;보다', 'I think/feel that(one''s assertion/opinion about a sit''n)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(1807, 'V(으)ㄴ 채로', '''while [still]'' (2nd cl occurs while state/action of 1st cl continues; emphasize state of unordinary/unexpected action continues; short form = (으)ㄴ 채; can''t combine with 가다/오다)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(1808, 'A(으)ㄴ지...A(으)ㄴ지V는지 ...V는지', '''whether/if... or...'' (asking/responding to ''whether or not'' ?s about fact/method)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(1809, 'N질', '''N-ing'' (the repeated act of using/doing N)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(1810, 'V아/어다가', '''so to / and then [somewhere else]'' (latter action done somewhere else using result of 1st action)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(1811, 'V(ㄴ)는/A다는 N', '''N said to be A/V (cl.)'' (adding indir. quoted content or 1''s thoughts describing N)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(1812, 'N(을)를 비롯해서 / 비롯한', '''starting with N / including N'' (1 representative item as example from many)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(1813, 'A/V(으)며; N(이)며', '''and'' & ''while'' (listing 2+ actions/states on equal terms, form/writ. OR simultaneous actions/states by same subj.)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(1814, 'N별', '''according to N'' (classified/grouped by N)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(1815, 'A/V거든; N(이)거든', '''if A/V/N [is true] then...'' (conditions/suppositions of the circumstance for next cl.; followed by imperatives/requests; casual only)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(1816, 'A/V았/었더라면; N였/이었더라면', '''if A/V had been...'' (if past event was different, result would be regrettable/fortunate in context; only past tense, only hypothetical)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(1817, 'A/V(으)ㅁ; N임', 'A/V/N occured/existed(recorded facts in document style or completed or decided/predeterm.; not all A/V can be used)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(1818, 'A(으)ㄴ / V는;N인;듯하다', '''I think / seems like...'' (conjecture about fact/sit''n, higher register/lit. than 는 것 같다)', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(1819, 'A하다 > A-히', 'adverb form for -하다-adjectives', 'grammar', '4A', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(1820, 'N일/A/V(으)ㄹ 리가 없다', '''there''s no way ... '' (st impossible in light of normal logic)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch10'),
(1821, 'V기가 무섭게', '''as soon as'' (narrating st ''seen'' & as soon as one event finished, another occurred, usually spoken, V in 2nd cl not Adj; exaggeration of -자마자)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch10'),
(1822, 'N(time) 만에', '''(time) later'' (emphasize action occurred after interval much shorter/longer than usual; often used w/ (으)ᄂ 지)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch10'),
(1823, 'A/V(으)나; N(이)나', '''Although ..., '' (contrast 2 opposite/contrary sit''ns/actions; mainly writ; same as -지만)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch10'),
(1824, 'A/V더라고요', '''I directly saw/experienced'' (fact newly known thru dir. xp; 반말= -더라)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch11'),
(1825, 'N치고', '''[all N w/o exception] OR ''for a N...'' (1. st/s1 w/o exception same as predicate; usually in negation & rhetorical 2. N is exceptional example all things considered)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch11'),
(1826, 'V(ㄴ)는/A다는 것은 N에서/N(으)로 알 수 있다', '''you can tell A/V by N'' (proof/basis 4 a result already occurred/sit''n that became known; can rearrange word order=-에서 -다는 것을 알 수 있다)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch11'),
(1827, 'N에 의하면', '''according to/ based on'' (attributing/citing source of info; usually followed by indir. quot''n; always present tense; usually form/writ; also -에 따르면)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch11'),
(1828, 'N력', 'power/ability to do N', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch11'),
(1829, 'V(으)려다가', '''I intended to V [but didn''t b/c reasons]'' (1. thinking about 1 action, but st makes it unfeasible, so different action done 2. changes/newly created sit''n or state)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch12'),
(1830, 'N(이)/A/V(으)ㄹ지도 모르다', '''might/may happen'' (not knowing certainty of sit''n/action, but guessing its possible but [usually] w/ low probability)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch12'),
(1831, 'N인가?A(으)ㄴ가?V는가?', 'written plain form ? ending (? ending in writ. lang. where ''-다/는다'' used as declarative)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch12'),
(1832, 'N마저', '''even N / the last remaining N'' (on top of existing sit''n even that N included or N the last thing remaining out of group; only negative contexts; -까지 can have same meaning)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch12'),
(1833, 'N되다', 'to become N', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch12'),
(1834, 'N1(이)면 N1, N2(이)면 N2', 'from N1 to N2 [both good]2+ things as examples & all equally good in context', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch13'),
(1835, 'V는 김에', 'while you''re at it...doing 1 action becomes opportunity for another originally unplanned but related action in 2nd cl.', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch13'),
(1836, 'V느니 차라리/아예', 'rather than V [2nd cl is preferable]both situations unfavorable, after xp 1 sit''n, following cl. is preferable; 차라리 can be omitted', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch13'),
(1837, 'N와/과 달리', 'unlike N [st else is ...]1 sit''n/circum different than another', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch13'),
(1838, 'N없이', 'without N', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch13'),
(1839, 'N에 따라서', 'depending on Nvarious sit''ns arise ''depending on'' a given standard/circumstance', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch14'),
(1840, 'A(으)냐에/V느냐에 따라서', 'depending on how/when/whatvarious sit''ns arise ''depending on'' a given standard/circumstance', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch14'),
(1841, 'A(으)ㄴ/V는 데다가', 'in addition to / moreover1 action/sit''n ''in addition to'' another of similar attribute; both cl same subj', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch14'),
(1842, 'A(으)ㄴ/V는 셈이다', 'You could say that / its more or less thatjudgement through assessment; ''reckoning'' about it', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch14'),
(1843, 'N에 불과하다', 'does not exceed Nsit''n doesn''t exceed certain standard/degree/quantity', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch14'),
(1844, 'N률/율', 'rate/ratio of N', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch14'),
(1845, 'N만 못하다', 'not the size/quality of Ncomparing 2 things & 1 not to the level of the other; same as N보다 못하다', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch15'),
(1846, 'V(으)ㄹ 게 아니라', 'not to V, but rather...rather than 1 action, another may be better; also: -만 -(으)ᄅ 게 아니라', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch15'),
(1847, 'N만 V(으)ㄹ 게 아니라', '"Not only will (someone) do N, but also..."rather than 1 action, another may be better책만 읽을 게 아니라 운동도 할 거예요. (Not only will I read books, but I will also exercise.)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch15'),
(1848, 'N(으)로서', 'as [the status of] an N...status, identity, & qualification of people/things; introducing topic, ''은/는 (으)로서 used & abbr. 은/는 (으)로', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch15'),
(1849, 'N(이)/A/V(으)므로', 'because (form/writ.)reason/basis for following st''mt about action/sit''n; can take 았/었; form/writ.', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch15'),
(1850, 'N심', 'feeling/sense of N', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch15'),
(1851, 'V(ㄴ)는/A다기보다는; N(이)라기보다는', 'rather than saying it''s A/V, its more like cl2rather than cl.1, 2nd cl. is better/more accurate; not opposites concepts', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch16'),
(1852, '설마 A/V겠어요?', 'Is it even possible that..? (disbelief)rhetorically emphasizing improbable conjectures', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch16'),
(1853, 'N(으)로부터', 'from N (form/writ)starting/departure point (writ/form)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch16'),
(1854, 'N에 의해서', 'due to N / [passive action] by Nstandard/means an action done; passive V often follows', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch16'),
(1855, '불-', 'no/not; un-/non-prefix (부+ㄷ/ㅈ)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch16'),
(1856, 'V(ㄴ)는/A다 싶다', 'to feel like / to wonderfeeling/thought based on perceived fact; (으)ㄹ까 싶다 used rhetorically w/ similar meaning', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch17'),
(1857, 'V곤 하다', 'often/usually/used to Vrepetition of action/sit''n', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch17'),
(1858, 'A/V았/었었-', 'did/had Vedstrongly express past events haven''t continued (similar to past perfect)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch17'),
(1859, 'V-곤 했다', 'used to Vto express an action that used to happen repeatedly in the past; indicates a habitual or regular action that is no longer occurring어렸을 때 방학 동안에 공부를 하는 대신에 하루 종일 게임을 하곤 했어요. When I was young, instead of studying during vacation, I used to play games all day.', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch17'),
(1860, 'V는 사이에', 'in the time it took to V...[st else happened]during span taken for 1 action; another occurs', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch17'),
(1861, 'V아/어 대다', 'excessively/continuously Vssit''n resulting from continued repeated/excessive action (neg. connotation)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch18'),
(1862, 'N(이)며 N2(이)며', '[such as/ike] N, N2, ...listing/connecting/grouping items indicating inclusion by common theme', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch18'),
(1863, 'A(으)ㄴ/V는 게 낫다', 'It''s better to be/do A/Vto express that doing something is better or preferable compared to other options. It often functions as advice or a recommendation, implying that one choice is the wiser or more beneficial one.일찍 자는 게 낫다. (It’s better to go to bed early.)깨끗한 게 낫다. (It’s better to be clean.)', 'grammar', '4B', 'Korean_grammar SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4B SNU.lvl.4B.ch18'),
(1864, '그 사람은 주말마다 영화를 본다고 했어요.', 'He said he watches movies every weekend.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1865, '민수 씨는 노래를 잘 부른다고 했어요.', 'Minsu said he sings the song well.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1866, '카렌 씨는 음식을 맛있게 만든다고 했어요.', 'Karen says she makes delicious food.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1867, '사진 두 장이 필요하다고 했어요.', 'They said they need two pictures.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1868, '''친구''라는 영화가 재밋있다고 했어요.', 'He said the movie called ''Friend'' was funny.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1869, '남대문시장이 싸다고 들었어요.', 'Heard Namdaemun Market is cheap.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1870, '춥다고 들었어요.', 'Heard it''s cold (there).', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1871, '독일에 산다고 들었어요.', 'Heard he''s living in Germany.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1872, '비빔밥을 잘 먹는다고 들었어요.', 'Heard that (he) often eats bibimbap.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1873, '4시라고 들었어요.', '(I) heard it''s at 4 o''clock.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1874, '열심히 공부해야겠어요.', 'I will and should study hard.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1875, '파티 준비를 해야겠어요.', 'I will and need to get ready for the party.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1876, '비행기 표를 예약해야겠어요.', 'I should and will book a flight.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1877, '잘라야겠어요.', 'I will and need to cut (my hair).', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1878, '연락해 봐야겠어요.', 'I should & will try contacting him.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1879, '따뜻하대요.', 'She said it''s warm. (abbr.)', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1880, '인기가 많대요.', 'He said it''s very popular. (abbr.)', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1881, '참석한대요.', 'She said she''s attending. (abbr.)', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1882, '매운 음식을 잘 먹는대요.', 'She said she eats spicy food often. (abbr.)', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1883, '한국어 선생님이래요.', 'She said she''s a Korean teacher. (abbr.)', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch1'),
(1884, '수업이 끝나자마자 먹어요.', 'As soon as class finishes, I eat.', 'phrase', '3A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU.lvl.3 SNU.lvl.3A SNU.lvl.3A.ch2'),
