(2728, '설악산은 단풍이 아름답다면서요?', 'Is what I heard true, Mt. Seorak has beautiful autumn leaves?', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2729, '한국학과에 합격했다면서요?', 'I heard you got accepted to the Korean department, is it true?', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2730, '열심히 일하다 보면 좋은 기회가 생길 거예요', 'If you keep working hard good opportunities will come up.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2731, '큰 소리로 읽다 보면 발음이 좋아질 거예요', 'If you keep reading out loud your pronunciation will improve.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2732, '한국 음식의 특징은 반찬이 많고 요리법이 다양하다는 것이다', 'The uinique characteristic of Korean food is that there are many side dishes and various recipes.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2733, '외국 생활에서 가장 힘든 점은 모든 일을 스스로 해결해야 한다는 점이다', 'The hardest thing about foreign life is that you have to solve everything on your own.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2734, '선생님께서 칭찬해 주신 나의 장점은 설실하고 책임감이 강하다는 것이다', 'The compliment my teacher gave me about my strength is that I''m faithful and have a strong sense of responsibility.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2735, '아이들은 부모가 하는 대로 따라 한다', 'Children follow what their parents do.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2736, '내가 조언해 준 내로 하면 어려운 문제도 쉽게 풀릴 것이다', 'If you do as I advised, difficult problems will be solved easily.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2737, '오늘 수업 시간에 학생들이 차례대로 자기소개를 했다', 'The students introduced themselves one after another in today''s class.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch1'),
(2738, '길이 어찌나 막히는지 한 시간이나 걸렸어요', 'The streets were so congested that it took me an hour.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2739, '요즘 어찌나 바쁜지 스트레스를 안 받을 수가 없어', 'I''ve been so busy lately that I can''t help but get stressed.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2740, '눈물이 날 정도로 매웠어요', 'It was spicy to the extent of causing tears.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2741, '어찌나 아픈지 허리를 못 펼 정도예요', 'It hurts so much to the point where I can''t stretch my back.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2742, '이렇게 돈을 많이 쓰다가는 생활비가 모자라게 될 수도 있다', 'If you continue spending this much money, you may end up short of living expenses.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2743, '계속 불규칙한 생활을 하다가는 건강이 나빠질 것이다', 'If you continue to live an irregular daily life, your health will deteriorate.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2744, '계획 없이 살다가는 나중에 후회하게 될 수도 있다', 'If you continue living without a plan, you may regret it later.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2745, '이 가게는 직원이 친절할 뿐만 아니라 물건의 질도 좋아서 항상 손님이 많다', 'At this store, not only are the employees kind, but the quality of the products is good, so there are always a lot of customers.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2746, '웃음은 병을 예방할 뿐만 아니라 병을 치료하기까지 한다', 'Laughter not only prevents illness but also treats it.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2747, '어른들뿐만 아니라 아이들도 스트레스를 많이 받을 수 있다', 'Not only adults but also children can be under a lot of stress.', 'phrase', '4A', 'Korean_pattern_practice SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch2'),
(2748, '이건 너무 얇아서 입으나 마나 소용없을 거야', 'It''s too thin, even without wearing it won''t make a difference. (I''ll still be cold)', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2749, '내가 보기에 이 경기는 해 보나 마나야. 실력 차이가 너무 나잖아.', 'There''s no use watching this game. There''s too much of a difference in skills.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2750, '옆 사람이 계속 전화를 받는 바람에 영화를 제대로 못 봤어요', 'The person next to me kept getting phone calls so I couldn''t properly watch the movie.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2751, '상대편이 반칙을 하는 바람에 넘어졌나 봐요', 'Because the other side cheated, I think that''s why he fell.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2752, '이것은 한국에서 유명한 닭갈비라는 음식입니다', 'This is a famous dish called Dakgalbi in Korea.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2753, '''서울의 별''이라는 드라마에서 1960년대 서울의 모습을 볼 수 있습니다', 'You can see the 1960s image of Seoul in the drama called "The Star of Seoul."', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2754, '풋살이라는 운동 경기에 대해 들어 본 적이 있습니까?', 'Have you ever heard of a sport called futsal?', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2755, '서울에 비해서 제주도는 날씨가 따뜻합니다', 'Compared to Seoul, the weather in Jeju Island is warm.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2756, '그 친구는 다른 친구들에 비해 젊어 보입니다', 'Compared to her other friends, that one looks younger', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2757, '그 선수는 실력에 비해 좋은 평가를 받지 못하고 있습니다', 'Compared to his ability, this athlete is not getting a good evaluation.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch3'),
(2758, '편리하기는커녕 너무 기능이 많아서 사용법도 모르겠어요', 'Far from being convenient, there are so many functions that I don''t even know how to use them.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2759, '(밀도 마) 갑자기 배탈이 나는 바람에 영화관은커녕 집 밖에도 못 나갔어', '(don''t say that) I suddenly had an upset stomach, so I couldn''t go out of the house, let alone the movie theater.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2760, '제목을 보니까 재미없을 게 뻔해', 'From the title, I''m sure it won''t be fun.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2761, '돈을 많이 써서 저축은커녕 생활비도 모자랄 게 뻔해요', 'I''ve spent a lot of money, so I''m surely short of living expenses, let alone saving money.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2762, '우리 집은 학교에서 가까운 반면에 지하철역에서 멀다', 'My house is close to the school, but on the other hand, its far from the subway station.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2763, '나는 책 읽는 것을 좋아하는 반면에 동생은 그림 그리는 것을 좋아한다', 'I like reading books whereas my younger sibling likes to draw pictures.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2764, '남자들은 보통 자동차에 관심이 많은 반면 여자들은 자동차에 별로 관심이 없는 편이다', 'Men usually have a lot of interest in cars, whereas women tend not to have an interest in cars.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2765, '촣은 재료로 만들었으니까 음식이 맛있을 수밖에 없다', 'It''s made with good ingredients, so the food must be delicious.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2766, '등록금이 없어서 대학 입학을 포기할 수밖에 없었다', 'Because I didn''t have tuition I had no choice but to give up going to college.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2767, '남자와 여자는 체격이 다르기 때문에 잘할 수 있는 운동이 다를 수밖에 없다', 'Men and women have different physiques, so the exercise they can do well is bound to be different.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch4'),
(2768, '오늘은 몸도 피곤하고 해서 집에서 쉬려고요', 'Most of all, I''m tired today, so I''m going to rest at home.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2769, '요즘 밥도 잘 안 먹고 해서 걱정이에요.', 'I''m worried because among other things, I haven''t been eating much lately.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2770, '친구가 도와준다더니 바쁜 일이 있다면서 그냥 가 버렸거든요', 'My friend said he would help but then he said there was an urgent work thing so he just left.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2771, '원숭이도 나무에서 떨어질 때가 있다더니 경험이 많은 지혜 씨도 실수를 하더라고요', 'They say even monkeys fall from trees, I''ve seen Ji-hye who has a lot of experience make mistakes.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2772, '소문은 눈덩이처럼 커지기 마련이다', 'Rumors are bound to snowball.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2773, '언어를 배우는 일은 시간이 걸리기 마련이다', 'It''s natural that learning a language takes time.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2774, '아무리 친한 친구라도 항상 같이 다니다 보면 마음이 안 맞을 때도 있기 마련이다', 'No matter how close your friends are, there''s bound to be times when you don''t get agree.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2775, '한국 사람을 자주 만나다 보니까 한국말을 잘하게 되었다', 'Because I meet up with Korean people often, I became good at Korean.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2776, '여러 종류의 책을 다양하게 읽다 보니 상식이 풍부해졌다', 'Constantly reading various kinds of books has enriched my common sense.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2777, '서로에게 모든 이야기를 하다 보니까 비밀이 없어졌다', 'After all the talking with each other there are no more secrets.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch5'),
(2778, '안 어렵기는요. 문법이 어려워서 매일 2시간씩 공부해야 해요', 'No, its not that its not difficult. Grammar is difficult, so I have to study for two hours every day.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2779, '잘하기는. 그냥 못 부른다는 소리는 안 들을 정도야', 'I''m not really that good. I just don''t listen when people say I can''t sing.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2780, '비가 오든지 눈이 오든지 경기 일정은 바뀌지 않을 거예요', 'Either rain or snow the game schedule won''t change.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2781, '한국 노래면 발라드든지 댄스곡이든지 상관없대요', 'If it''s a Korean song, it doesn''t matter if it''s either a ballad or dance music', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2782, '부모님이야말로 내가 가장 존경하는 분이다', 'My parents are the very ones I respect the most.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2783, '한글이야말로 세계 최고의 문자이다', 'Hangul indeed is the best alphabet in the world.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2784, '아리랑이야말로 한국을 대표하는 노래이다', 'Arirang indeed is the representative song of Korea.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2785, '우리 반 학생들은 여간 똑똑한 것이 아니다', 'The students in my class are not the ordinary amount of smart.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2786, '오랜만에 친구를 다시 만나서 여간 기쁘지 않았다', 'Meeting up with a friend after a long time wasn''t just your ordinary happiness.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2787, '내 동생은 여간 공부를 열심히 하는 것이 아니다', 'My younger sibling isn''t doing the ordinary study hard thing.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch6'),
(2788, '힘들더라도 포기하지 말고 끝까지 해 보세요', 'Even if it''s hard, don''t give up and try your best.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2789, '괜찮아요 이번에 지더라도 한 번 더 기회가 있잖아요', 'It''s ok, even if you lose this time, you have one more chance.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2790, '이무리 배가 고프더라도 도둑질을 하면 안 된다고 봐요', 'No matter how much and even if you''re hungry, you shouldn''t steal.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2791, '저는 두 사람이 사랑하면 나이 차이는 중요하지 않다고 봐요', 'I don''t think the age difference is important when two people love each other.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2792, '전화가 끊어질까 봐 신발을 신은 채로 집으로 뛰어 들어갔다', 'I was afraid the phone would cut out so I ran into the house still wearing my shoes', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2793, '어제는 너무 피곤해서 옷도 갈아입지 않은 채 잠이 들었다', 'I was so tired yesterday that I fell asleep without changing my clothes.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2794, '지하철 안에서 문에 기댄 채로 음식을 먹고 있는 사람들을 자주 볼 수 있다', 'You can often see people eating food while leaning against the door on the subway.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2795, '부모님께 전화하면 몸이 아픈지 안 아픈지 계속 물어보신다', 'When I call my parents, they keep asking me if I''m sick or not.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2796, '히엔 씨가 빨간색을 좋아하는지 노란색을 좋아하는지 잘 모르겠어요', 'I don''t know if Hee-yen likes red or yellow.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2797, '여기에서 시청역이 가까운지 광화문역이 가까운지 확인해 보세요', 'Check whether City Hall station is close or Gwanghwamun station is close from here.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch7'),
(2798, '전에는 담가 먹었는데 요즘은 사다가 먹어요', 'I used to make [kimchi] but these days I buy it to eat [somewhere else].', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2799, '산 게 아니에요. 친구에게서 빌려다 입은 거예요.', 'I didn''t buy it. I borrowed it [somewhere else] from a friend and wore it.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2800, '저도 직접 연락은 못 했는데 유학 준비를 한다는 소문을 들었어요', 'I didn''t get in touch with him myself, but I heard rumors saying that he was preparing to study abroad.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2801, '거기 가면 싸고 좋은 물건이 많다는 말을 들어서요', 'I hear talk saying there''s a lot of good cheap stuff there.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2802, '세계에는 아시아, 유럽을 비롯해서 모두 6대륙이 있다', 'In the world, including Asia and Europe, all together there are 6 major continents.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2803, '이번 회의에는 한국을 비롯한 10개국 대표들이 참석했다', 'At this meeting, including Korea, 10 countries attended.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2804, '설날에 한국 사람은 윷놀이를 비롯해서 다양한 민속놀이를 한다', 'On New Year''s Day, Koreans play various folk games including yut nori.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2805, '이 도서관에는 디자인 관련 책이 많으며 세계 여러 나라의 잡지도 많이 있다', 'In this library, there are many design-related books and many magazines from many countries around the world.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2806, '배가 아프고 소화가 안되며 속이 거북할 때 손을 따면 효과가 있다', 'When you have a stomachache, indigestion, and bloating, if you lift your hands it can be effective.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2807, '이 민족은 아이들이 어머니의 성을 따르며 재산도 딸이 물려받는다', 'In these societies, children follow their mothers'' surnames and pass their wealth to their daughters.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch8'),
(2808, '무슨 일이 있거든 먼저 엄마한테 연락해야 한다. 알겠지?', 'If something happens, contact me [your mother] first. Ok?', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2809, '콘서트 소식을 듣거든 저한테도 알려 주세요.', 'If you hear news about the concert, then please let me know.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2810, '조금만 더 늦었더라면 비행기를 놓칠 뻔했어', 'If I was a little later, I would have missed my flight.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2811, '우리가 10분만 일찍 도착했더라면 지금 시작하는 영화를 볼수 있었는데.', 'If we had arrived 10 minutes earlier, we could have seen the movie that starts now.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2812, '이곳은 안개가 자주 끼기 때문에 교통사고가 자주 발생함', 'Because of frequent fogs here, traffic accidents occur frequently.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2813, '시험 기간에는 관계자 외에는 이 사무실에 들어오지 못함', 'During the exam period, except for authorities, entrance to the office is not possible.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2814, '대학 졸업 후 50여 개국을 여행하면서 작품 활동 중임', 'After graduating from university, he has traveled to more than 50 countries and is working on his work.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2815, '마리코 씨는 요즘 회사 일 때문에 스트레스가 많은 듯하다', 'These days Mariko seems to be under a lot of stress because of her company work.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2816, '어머니가 주무시는 듯해서 조용히 준비를 하고 학교에 갔다', 'My mother seemed to be sleeping, so I quietly got ready and went to school.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2817, '이 작는 내년에 새로운 작품을 가지고 귀국할 듯하다', 'Next year, this writer is likely to return home with a new work.', 'vocab', '4A', 'SNU SNU.lvl.4 SNU.lvl.4A SNU.lvl.4A.ch9'),
(2818, '대학교 입학을 결정하는 시험인데 쉬울 리가 없어', 'It''s a college entrance exam, there''s no way it can be easy.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::37_4B_A/V(으)ㄹ_리가_없다_-_there''s_no_way_that'),
(2819, '제 여자 친구는 일본에 있는데요. 제 여자 친구가 왔을 리가 있갰어요?', 'My girlfriend is in Japan. Is there anyway my girlfriend could have come? [rhetorical]', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::37_4B_A/V(으)ㄹ_리가_없다_-_there''s_no_way_that'),
(2820, '수업 끝나기가 무섭게 나가던데요', 'As soon as class was over she left.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::38_4B_V기가_무섭게_-_''as_soon_as''_usually_spoken'),
(2821, '서점에 진열하기가 무섭게 다 팔린대요', 'At the book store, as soon as they put them on display, they sell out.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::38_4B_V기가_무섭게_-_''as_soon_as''_usually_spoken'),
(2822, '대학을 졸업한 지 1년 만에 취직했다', 'I graduated college, 1 year later I got a job.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::39_4B_(time)_N_만에_-_cl2_occurs_(time)_after_cl1'),
(2823, '한국 전쟁 때 헤어진 가족을 50년 만에 다시 만났다', 'I met my family who separated during the Korean War again after 50 years.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::39_4B_(time)_N_만에_-_cl2_occurs_(time)_after_cl1'),
(2824, '비싸게 장만한 컴퓨터가 산 지 일주일 만에 고장이 났다', 'The expensive computer I bought broke down one week later.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::39_4B_(time)_N_만에_-_cl2_occurs_(time)_after_cl1'),
(2825, '이 우산은 가벼워서 들고 다니기 좋으나 찢어지기 쉽다는 단점이 있다', 'Although this umbrella is light so it''s easy to carry around, it has a disadvantage in that it can tear easily.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::40_4B_A/V(으)나,_N(이)나_-_Although_A/V/N'),
(2826, '두 달 동안 회사를 살리려고 열심히 노력했으나 결국 실패하고 말았다', 'Although I tried hard to revive the company for two months, it ended up failing after all.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::40_4B_A/V(으)나,_N(이)나_-_Although_A/V/N'),
(2827, '백화점 물건은 값은 비싼 편이나 품질이 좋다', 'Although department store items tend to be expensive, they have good quality.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::40_4B_A/V(으)나,_N(이)나_-_Although_A/V/N'),
(2828, '전에 먹어 봤는데 참 맛있더라고.', 'I tried it before [and I experienced that] it was really delicious.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::41_4B_A/V더라고요_-_directly_saw/experienced'),
(2829, '요즘 젊은 사람들이 많이 쓰더라고요.', '[as I have experienced] Young people use it a lot these days.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::41_4B_A/V더라고요_-_directly_saw/experienced'),
(2830, '역시 싼 불건치고 푸질이 좋은 것은 없군요.', 'As expected, for the price, there''s nothing good quality.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::42_4B_N치고_-_all_N_w/o_exception_OR_for_a_N...'),
(2831, '요즘 많이 쓰는 줄임말인데 젊은 사람치고 저 말을 모르는 사람은 거의 없어요.', 'These days it''s a much used portmanteau, there''s almost not a single young person who doesn''t know it.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::42_4B_N치고_-_all_N_w/o_exception_OR_for_a_N...'),
(2832, '날씨가 춥다는 것은 사람들의 옷차림에서 알 수 있다.', 'You can tell the weather''s cold from peoples outfits.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::43_4B_V(ᄂ)는/A다는_것은_N에서_알_수_있다_-_can_tell_by'),
(2833, '그 사람이 책을 많이 읽는다는 것은 사용하는 어휘에서 알 수 있다.', 'You can tell she reads a lot by the vocabulary she uses.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::43_4B_V(ᄂ)는/A다는_것은_N에서_알_수_있다_-_can_tell_by'),
(2834, '사람의 성격은 운전하는 습관으로 알 수 있다.', 'You can tell a persons personality from their driving habits.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::43_4B_V(ᄂ)는/A다는_것은_N에서_알_수_있다_-_can_tell_by'),
(2835, '정부의 발표에 의하면 내년부터 대학 입학시험이 바뀔 것이라고 한다.', 'According to the government''s announcement, the university entrance exam will change starting next year', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::44_4B_N에_의하면_-_according_to_N,_based_on_N'),
(2836, '교수님 말씀에 의하면 옛날에는 줄임말을 사용하지 않았다고 한다.', 'According to the professor, portmanteaus were not used in the past.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::44_4B_N에_의하면_-_according_to_N,_based_on_N'),
(2837, '실험 결과에 의하면 부정적인 말이 기억에 더 오래 남는다고 한다.', 'According to the results of the experiment, negative words remain in memory longer.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::44_4B_N에_의하면_-_according_to_N,_based_on_N'),
(2838, '고쳐서 쓰려다가 싸게 나온 제품이 있어서 새로 샀어요', 'I was going to fix it and use it, but a cheap one came out, so I just bought a new one.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::45_4B_V(으)려다가_-_intended_to,_but_reasons_made_impos'),
(2839, '가지 말라고 붙잡으려다 급한 일이 있는 것 같아서 그냥 가라고 했어요', 'I tried to hold on to him [keep him here], but I thought he was in a hurry, so I told him to go.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::45_4B_V(으)려다가_-_intended_to,_but_reasons_made_impos'),
(2840, '내일은 오늘보다 더 추울지도 몰라요.', 'Tomorrow might be colder than today.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::46_4B_A/V(으)ㄹ지도_모르다_-_might/may'),
(2841, '쓰던 것을 버리고 자꾸 새로 사면 이 세상이 온통 쓰레기로 덮일지도 몰라요.', 'If you throw away used things and buy new repeatedly, the whole world might be covered with trash.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::46_4B_A/V(으)ㄹ지도_모르다_-_might/may'),
(2842, '이 글을 읽고 있는 당신은 지금 행복한가?', 'Are you happy reading this?', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::47_4B_A(으)ㄴ/V는가?_-_writ._plain_form_?'),
(2843, '컴퓨터는 인간의 생활에 어떤 영향을 주는가?', 'How do computers influence human life?', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::47_4B_A(으)ㄴ/V는가?_-_writ._plain_form_?'),
(2844, '우리는 하루에 얼마나 많은 일회용품을 사용하고 있는가?', 'How many disposables do we use a day?', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::47_4B_A(으)ㄴ/V는가?_-_writ._plain_form_?'),
(2845, '가장 친한 친구마저 나를 의심하는 것 같았다.', 'Even my best friend seemed suspicious of me.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::48_4B_N마저_-_even_N_incl._/_last_remaining_N'),
(2846, '오랫동안 비가 오지 않아서 강물마저 말라 버렸다', 'It hasn''t rained for a long time, so even the river has dried up.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::48_4B_N마저_-_even_N_incl._/_last_remaining_N'),
(2847, '쓰레기 때문에 땅이 계속 오염되면 우리가 살 땅마저 없어질지도 모른다', 'If the land continues to be polluted by garbage, we may lose the last remaining land we live in.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::48_4B_N마저_-_even_N_incl._/_last_remaining_N'),
(2848, '공부면 공부, 운동이면 운동, 못하는 게 없어요.', 'From studying to exercise, there''s nothing I can''t do.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::49_4B_N1(이)면_N1,_N2(이)면_N2_-_from_N1_to_N2_[both_good'),
(2849, '산이면 산, 바다면 바다, 다 좋더라고요.', 'From the mountain to the sea, [I discovered] everything was good.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::49_4B_N1(이)면_N1,_N2(이)면_N2_-_from_N1_to_N2_[both_good'),
(2850, '방 청소하는 심에 책상 정리도 좀 해.', 'Clean your room and organize your desk while you''re at it.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::50_4B_V는_김에_-_while_you''re_at_it'),
(2851, '어머니 선물 사러 백화점에 산 김에 예쁜 장갑이 있어서 같이 샀어요.', 'I went to by my mom''s gift at the department store and there were pretty gloves, so I bought them too while I was at it.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::50_4B_V는_김에_-_while_you''re_at_it'),
(2852, '평범한 여행을 하느니 차라리 여행을 안 가는 게 낫다고 생각한다.', 'Rather than go on a plain trip, I think it''s better not to go on a trip.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::51_4B_V느니_차라리_-_rather_do_2nd_cl.'),
(2853, '이렿게 막히는 시간에 택시를 타느니 차라리 걸어가는 게 낫겠다.', 'Rather than take a taxi during this rush hour I''ll walk.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::51_4B_V느니_차라리_-_rather_do_2nd_cl.'),
(2854, '그렇게 비싸기만 하고 맛이 없는 식당에서 밥을 먹느니 차라리 굶겠다.', 'I would rather starve than eat at such an expensive and tasteless restaurant.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::51_4B_V느니_차라리_-_rather_do_2nd_cl.'),
(2855, '우리 언니는 수영을 잘하지만 나는 언니와 달리 수영에 소질이 없다.', 'My sister is good at swimming, but unlike my sister, I don''t have a talent for swimming.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::52_4B_N과/와_달라_-_unlike_N_[st_else_is...]'),
(2856, '다른 지역과 달리 이 지역에서는 휴대폰이 잘 안된다.', 'Unlike other regions, cell phones do not work well in this area.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::52_4B_N과/와_달라_-_unlike_N_[st_else_is...]'),
(2857, '그박물관은 지난번에 갔을 때와 달리 관람객이 너무 많아서 줄을 서서 기다려야 했다.', 'Unlike the last time I went to the museum, there were so many visitors that I had to wait in line.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::52_4B_N과/와_달라_-_unlike_N_[st_else_is...]'),
(2858, '지역에 따라서 집값에 차이가 있어요.', 'Depending on the region, house prices have a difference.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::53_4B_N에_따라서_-_depending_on_N'),
(2859, '거리에 따라 지하철 요금이 달라요.', 'Depending on the street subway fare is different.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::53_4B_N에_따라서_-_depending_on_N'),
(2860, '성격이 쾌활한 데다가 친절해서 친구들이 다 좋아해요.', 'In addition to a cheerful personality, she is kind, so all her friends like her.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::54_4B_A(으)ㄴ/V는_데다가_-_in_addition_to'),
(2861, '물가가 인상된 데다가 기름값까지 올라서 버스 요금을 올릴 수밖에 없대요.', 'In addition to prices increasing to gas prices going up, bus fare has no other option but to go up.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::54_4B_A(으)ㄴ/V는_데다가_-_in_addition_to'),
(2862, '이 식당은 다른 곳보다 비싸긴 하지만 맛이나 서비스를 생각하면 싼 셈이다.', 'This restaurant is more expensive than other places but thinking about the taste and service, you could say it''s cheap.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::55_4B_A(으)ㄴ/V는_셈이다_-_more_or_less,_you_could_say_that'),
(2863, '이번 수학여행은 우리 반에서 한 명 빼고 다 가니까 거의 다 가는 셈이다.', 'Since all but one person went on the school field trip you could almost say everyone went.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::55_4B_A(으)ㄴ/V는_셈이다_-_more_or_less,_you_could_say_that'),
(2864, '그 사람은 3주가 넘게 입원해 있었으니까 이번 달에는 거의 일을 못 한 셈이다.', 'Since he''s been hospitalized for more than three weeks, you could almost say he couldn''t work this month.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::55_4B_A(으)ㄴ/V는_셈이다_-_more_or_less,_you_could_say_that'),
(2865, '인터넷에 돌아다니는 이야기는 소문에 불과하니까 믿지 않는 것이 좋다.', 'Since stories that go around the internet are no more than rumors, its better not to believe them.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::56_4B_N에_불과하다_-_not_exceeding_N_(lit_&_fig)'),
(2866, '한 달에 책을 한 권 이상 읽는 사람은 20%에 불과한 것으로 나타났다.', 'It appears that no more than 20% of people read more than one book per month.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::56_4B_N에_불과하다_-_not_exceeding_N_(lit_&_fig)'),
(2867, '회사에서는 무섭고 엄한 상사이지만 집에서는 평범한 아버지에 불과하다.', 'He''s a scary and strict boss at work, but he''s no more than a normal dad at home.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::56_4B_N에_불과하다_-_not_exceeding_N_(lit_&_fig)'),
(2868, '불경기라서 올해는 작년만 못해요. 손님이 많이 줄었어요.', 'Because it''s a bad economy, this year isn''t the same as last year. The amount of customers has decreased a lot.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::57_4B_N만_못하다_-_not_the_the_level_of_N'),
(2869, '여러 명이 같이 생활하니까 혼자 살 때만 못해요.', 'Since living together with many people, living alone doesn''t compare.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::57_4B_N만_못하다_-_not_the_the_level_of_N'),
(2870, '피곤하다고 잠만 잘 게 아니라 나가서 운동을 좀 하세요.', 'Don''t just take a nap because you''re tired, go out and exercise a little.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::58_4B_V(으)ㄹ_게_아니라_-_not_V_but../instead_of_V'),
(2871, '무조건 싫다고 할 게 아니라 좋은 점은 없는지 생각해 보세요.', 'Don''t say you don''t like it without reason, think about whether there'' are any good point.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::58_4B_V(으)ㄹ_게_아니라_-_not_V_but../instead_of_V'),
(2872, '동생이 옳지 않은 판단을 할 때는 언니로서 조언을 해 줄 필요가 있다.', 'You need to give advice as an older sister when your younger brother makes wrong decisions.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::59_4B_N(으)로서_-_as_an_N_[as_the_status_of_N]'),
(2873, '그 선수가 경기 중에 다친 것을 보고 오래전부터 좋아한 팬으로서 마음이 아팠다.', 'As a fan who''s liked him for a long time, seeing that athlete get injured in the middle of a game was heartbreaking.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::59_4B_N(으)로서_-_as_an_N_[as_the_status_of_N]'),
(2874, '무궁화는 한국의 국화로서 옛날부터 한국인의 사랑을 받아 왔다.', 'Hibiscus, as the national flower of Korea, has come to be loved by Koreans since a long time ago.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::59_4B_N(으)로서_-_as_an_N_[as_the_status_of_N]'),
(2875, '가을이 되면 시원해지고 날씨도 좋으므로 야외 활동을 하는 사람들이 많다.', 'The weather in autumn gets cooler and nicer so there are many people who do outdoor activities.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::60_4B_A/V(으)므로_-_because_(form./writ.)'),
(2876, '이 영화는 무서운 장면이 많이 나오므로 노약자나 임신부는 보지 않는 것이 좋다.', 'This movie has many scary scenes, so it is better for elderly or pregnant women not to watch.', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::60_4B_A/V(으)므로_-_because_(form./writ.)'),
(2877, '무궁화는 쏯이 100일 동안 계속 피므로 ''끝이 없다''는 뜻의 이름을 가지게 되었다.', 'Because it continues to bloom for 100 days, Hibiscus has a name meaning, ''endless.''', 'vocab', '', 'Import_pattern_pracitce_korean_2 missing-media 서울대_한국어_문연습_SNU_Korean_Pattern_Practice::60_4B_A/V(으)므로_-_because_(form./writ.)');
